<TITLE> 41 civil servants shuffled </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Jan 2 (bdnews24.com)  The government has transferred one secretary, one additional secretary, two joint secretaries, 35 deputy secretaries and two senior assistant secretaries, the establishment ministry said in a statement Wednesday. Post and telecommunication secretary Sheikh Khurshid Alam has been transferred to the Local Government Division. The post fell vacant as the previous LGD secretary Safarraz Hossain went on leave preparatory to retirement on Dec 30. Nobody was appointed to fill the post until Wednesday. The managing director of state-owned Sadharan Bima Corporation, Ilias Ahmed, has been appointed to the industry ministry as additional secretary. The previous additional secretary of the industry ministry, Dr Ayub Mia, was earlier appointed to the food ministry as acting secretary. bdnews
